name: Cauliflower
description: Cauliflower is as good a source of fiber and vitamins.Its ingredients may help strengthen bones, boost the cardiovascular system, and prevent cancer.

name: Red Tomato
description: The tomato is consumed in diverse ways, including raw, as an ingredient in many dishes, sauces, salads, and drinks. it is considered a vegetable for culinary purposes.

name: Orange
description: Fruit grown in warmer doesn't develop a deep orange color. Cold nighttime temperatures cause citrus to show deep orange color, and when the weather warms up again in late spring and early summer.

name: Barari Dates
description: Barari (Tunisian) Dates called as “Queen of The Dates” also Barari  original Tunisian dates freshly imported from Tunisia. No artificial additives or preservatives have been used in them.

name: Litchi
description: Litchi benefits include its ability to aid in weight loss, protect the skin, boost the immune system, prevent cancer, improve digestion, build strong bones, lower blood pressure, defend the body against viruses, improve circulation, and optimize metabolic activities.

name: Meat
description: Meat, such as beef, is mainly composed of protein. Usually eaten as roasts, ribs, or steaks, beef is also commonly ground or minced. Patties of ground beef are often used in hamburgers.

name: Egg
description: Duck Eggs are an all-natural source of high-quality protein and a number of other nutrients. Duck egg is a good source of Protein, Riboflavin, Folate, Iron and Phosphorus, and a very good source of Vitamin B12 and Selenium.

name: Palong Shak
description: Bright, vibrant-looking spinach leaves are not only more appealing to the eye but more nourishing as well. Spinach has good levels of iron.

name: Cucumber
description: Few foods are as cool as a cucumber.While most people think of cucumbers as vegetables, they are actually a fruit.Cucumbers are naturally low in calories

name: Onions
description: Though all vegetables are important for health, certain kinds offer unique benefits. Onions are members of the Allium genus of flowering plants.
